│ inserted casts) prefers VF=16.\n\n2. Analyzing opt's Log:\nScalarEvolution    │
│ shows the loop has backedge-taken count -1 (unknown), so MaxTripCount=0 in    │
│ cost comparison logic. The cost comparison in isMoreProfitable reduces to     │
│ (CostA * WidthB) < (CostB * WidthA). VPlan cost queries (observed via         │
│ debugger): cost(VF=2)=5, cost(VF=4)=4, cost(VF=16)=18. Legacy model chose     │
│ VF=16 (its expectedCost for large VF is lower per element since it ignores    │
│ newly added casts). Assertion checks: BestFactor.Width(=4) !=                 │
│ LegacyVF.Width(=16) and planContainsAdditionalSimplifications(...) returns    │
│ false, so it fires.\n\n3. Root Cause                                          │
│ Analysis:\nplanContainsAdditionalSimplifications only detects removed         │
│ instructions (instructions existing in the original loop but not represented  │
│ by any recipe and not skipped). It does NOT account for extra instructions    │
│ introduced by VPlan-only transformations (e.g., VPWidenCastRecipe generated   │
│ trunc/zext for narrowed reductions, VPInstruction::ComputeReductionResult,    │
│ extract-from-end). These added recipes have no underlying original IR         │
│ instruction (GetInstructionForCost returns null), so they are invisible to    │
│ the simplification detector. As a result, legitimate divergences due to added │
│ code (increasing cost at higher VFs) are misclassified, and the assertion     │
│ wrongly triggers.\n\nTherefore, the contract of the assertion is too narrow:  │
│ It only tolerates differences when there are simplifications (reductions in   │
│ code) but not when there are additions of code that the legacy model never    │
│ modeled. The cost disagreement here is expected and should be                 │
│ permitted.\n\n4. Proposed Edit Points:\nEdit Point 1 (lines 7408-7453):       │
│ Extend planContainsAdditionalSimplifications to also return true if the VPlan │
│ introduces additional executable recipes that generate IR not present in the  │
│ original loop and not accounted for by the legacy cost model. Concretely,     │
│ scan the recipes for those producing vector IR (e.g., VPWidenCastRecipe,      │
│ VPInstruction with opcodes like ComputeReductionResult, ExtractFromEnd) with  │
│ no underlying original Instruction and not ephemeral; if any exist, treat as  │
