│ infrastructure) and whose GetInstructionForCost returns nullptr.\n- If        │
│ AddedCode is true, return true early.\n\nEdit Point 2 (lines 7516-7523):      │
│ Adjust the assertion condition to allow mismatch if either the existing       │
│ simplification predicate is true OR newly detected additional generated code  │
│ predicate is true. Introduce a helper (or incorporate into existing function) │
│ and update the assertion accordingly.\n\n5. Conclusion:\nBy broadening the    │
│ mismatch tolerance to include cases where VPlan adds extra code not modeled   │
│ by the legacy cost model, the assertion no longer fires for legitimate        │
│ divergences like the narrowed reduction casts. The fix preserves verification │
│ intent (flag true unexpected discrepancies) while avoiding false positives    │
│ when added recipes affect cost differently across VFs. This stabilizes        │
│ loop-vectorize under the new cost model for patterns introducing auxiliary    │
│ vector-only instructions.\n"                                                  │
